{\b0 \cf31 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b1 \cf34 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_synopsis_1}{\*\bkmkend co_synopsis_1}
{\b1 \cf34 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb400 
Synopsis
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf31 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf31 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf31 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Developer brought declaratory judgment action against city for approval of its development plans. The Circuit Court, Alachua County, George H. Pierce, J., rendered final declaratory judgment and city appealed. The District Court of Appeal, Ervin, J., held that: (1) city never took final action in its approval process and Circuit Court lacked subject matter jurisdiction over action, and (2) it could not be said that developer\rquote s further pursuit of remedies within city\rquote s plan development approval process would have been to no avail.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf31 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf31 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf31 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf31 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Reversed.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf31 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf31 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b1 \cf31 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf31 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Procedural Posture(s):
}
}
{\b0 \cf31 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 On Appeal.
\par 
}
}
