}\b0 \cf31 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \ql \li30 \fs20 \intbl \cell \row }
{\trowd \lastrow \trleft0 
\clpadt30 \clpadft3 \clpadr30 \clpadfr3 \clbrdrb \clbrdrl \trql \clwWidth600 \cellx600 
\clpadt30 \clpadft3 \clpadr30 \clpadfr3 \clbrdrb \clbrdrr \trql \clwWidth4040 \cellx4640 
\intbl 
{\ri30 \li30 
{\b0 \cf31 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \ql \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf31 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 
}
}
}\b0 \cf31 \f2 \ri30 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \ql \li30 \fs20 \intbl \cell \intbl 
{\ri30 \li30 
{\b0 \cf31 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \ql \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf31 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf31 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf31 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf31 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb0 
Developer which brought declaratory judgment action against city regarding development plans had remedies within city\rquote s planned redevelopment approval process, the further pursuit of which could not be said to have been to no avail, and thus, circuit court lacked subject matter jurisdiction over action, where developer had right to present evidence and arguments regarding development at public hearings prior to final action by city on developer\rquote s site plans.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf31 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li30 
{\*\bkmkstart co_headnoteId_19851594270032018020612213}{\*\bkmkend co_headnoteId_19851594270032018020612213}
